<subSubSection id="A148745A373255D8B87F46E70872EBFB" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="62AAF6B91517B082E1D89501D881DADA" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
<taxonomicName id="A242322C3E96BA6F2F47A884D69AFAFC" LSID="http://zoobank.org/6A3DCAC3-1857-4AA6-8A72-0F0C20D4B50F" authority=")" authorityName="Roza &amp; Schrago &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" genus="Mesochila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mesochila (Neomesochila)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Neomesochila">Mesochila (Neomesochila)</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="6ACDBC6FF88DC8104516FD8EAFF2B793" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">subgen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2D4D0F14C479281E8CD142D5DCBB2C1A" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="type species">
<paragraph id="CAEB2198432BE578A94BCE5084CDF1BD" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="96F1B5ED7AD0F33B0D97DF0B24BE42CA" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
<taxonomicName id="8C3946E2FCF3164275917D9CD30E6AAD" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Odontocheila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Odontocheila brevipennis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipennis">
<emphasis id="1530E489AFFE85F2030C9EF746E268B9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Odontocheila brevipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
W. Horn, 1907
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7E3ED666CEB9CCD7363906F99D75DC63" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="D6674370F221829AC12C0C399A3EDB26" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BDFDFB20B54F66B34F0E71DBBB8420BE" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
Composed word formed by 
<emphasis id="B7EA8441B93AA11CA251A4A44373B66C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">neo</emphasis>
(from Greek, means new) and 
<taxonomicName id="A19AAC48CC212FB00A5C921F9D7252B5" authorityName="Rivalier" authorityYear="1969" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" genus="Mesochila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mesochila" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="354BDEA3B1706F6DFFD698264A8A2895" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Mesochila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the genus name.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B9E06D4EB08DA1DE3A9F120B7A4CB9E7" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C44F15506D858EE191326139D59E0FE9" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="06EE21199F9B9190C9945267BF740E2E" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Smaller body length, usually between 6-9.3 mm; mandibles with four teeth (plus molar one); pronotum as wide as long; elytra 3.3-3.6 times longer than wide, finely punctate; aedeagus thin, with apical third subparallel, with apex forming distinctly wide bent rounded beak, internal sac containing stingray-like ventral spur and an oval feebly sclerotized central sclerite.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D85523C5902B34E46129F529056062FE" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis id="F933230596F9D1F8545D1A00FD402D10" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">4 species included</emphasis>
:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9CA3451B2D526260EA0D05674DBE7F29" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
· 
<taxonomicName id="ACD5152B49474395C491105E24DC81E9" genus="M." lsidName="M. (N.) brevipennis" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" rank="species" species="brevipennis" subGenus="N.">M. (N.) brevipennis</taxonomicName>
(W. Horn, 1907)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="56104BCAD67C872352FAA11B5B3AC2A3" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
· 
<taxonomicName id="51D90197FA69B3026F9F35D84E781ABC" genus="M." lsidName="M. (N.) drechseli" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" rank="species" species="drechseli" subGenus="N.">M. (N.) drechseli</taxonomicName>
(Sawada and Wiesner, 1997)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0DE7ABFBA32A9E455C0AEBD03F3A421E" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
· 
<taxonomicName id="805839E89729A83F28DCA8624C440ABF" genus="M." lsidName="M. (N.) moraveci" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" rank="species" species="moraveci" subGenus="N.">M. (N.) moraveci</taxonomicName>
(Roza and Mermudes, 2019)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="415DA1FB1240CDA848CD87BCE9F3245D" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
· 
<taxonomicName id="4466E83772DC2313543897EF2CCFFFC6" genus="M." lsidName="M. (N.) prepusula" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" rank="species" species="prepusula" subGenus="N.">M. (N.) prepusula</taxonomicName>
(W. Horn, 1907)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="421FF7AA80B5F441EA9244D9F9DEA3E8" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" type="notes">
<paragraph id="1CBEFFF5C10EC2A6004B1FEDDCBB79BB" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="73EC2B47B7526E84FFFC3A9D2B41EA08" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
It is interesting to point out that the stingray-like ventral spur (term proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="A0AEB5B2BC388D4101E9C5F483146E61" author="Moravec, J" journalOrPublisher="Acta Musei Moraviae, Scientiae Biologicae (Brno)" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="127 - 206" refId="B30" refString="Moravec, J, 2018a. Taxonomic and nomenclatorial revision within the Neotropical genera of the subtribe Odontocheilina W. Horn in a new sense - 20. Beckerium W. Horn stat. restit., Mesochila Rivalier stat. nov. and Poecilochila Rivalier stat. nov. Acta Musei Moraviae, Scientiae Biologicae (Brno) 103 (2): 127 - 206" title="Taxonomic and nomenclatorial revision within the Neotropical genera of the subtribe Odontocheilina W. Horn in a new sense - 20. Beckerium W. Horn stat. restit., Mesochila Rivalier stat. nov. and Poecilochila Rivalier stat. nov." volume="103" year="2018 a">Moravec 2018a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="AA9E788D1EF2E51CEFB9FE0D35DEDC67" author="Moravec, J." journalOrPublisher="Biosfericka rezervace Dolni Morava: Lednice na Morave, Czech Republic" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" refId="B32" refString="Moravec, J., 2020. . Taxonomic revision of the Neotropical tiger beetle genera of the subtribe Odontocheilina - Volume 2. A complete revision of other twelve genera of the subtribe (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). Biosfericka rezervace Dolni Morava: Lednice na Morave, Czech Republic" title=". Taxonomic revision of the Neotropical tiger beetle genera of the subtribe Odontocheilina - Volume 2. A complete revision of other twelve genera of the subtribe (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae)." year="2020">2020</bibRefCitation>
), one of the most distinct features of 
<taxonomicName id="AD052B3629317D751D6DA53448CCDC50" authority="" genus="M." lsidName="M. (Mesochila)" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Mesochila">M. (Mesochila)</taxonomicName>
, present in almost all species previous to this study, was found to be homoplastic, with independent origins in 
<taxonomicName id="4B25B574E6D10D173E5173102A462F2F" authority="" genus="M." lsidName="M. (Neomesochila)" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Neomesochila">M. (Neomesochila)</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="4FACDD6000E929DFAC4D64210E40469D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">subgen. nov.</emphasis>
and inside 
<taxonomicName id="72290923BCD599B1E63D8E6DF3643D71" authority="" genus="M." lsidName="M. (Mesochila)" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Mesochila">M. (Mesochila)</taxonomicName>
, derived from bifurcate or u-shaped ventral spurs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9387EF4A931F019DF5AEB44CF689B82E" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">
Finally, it is important to highlight that the outgroup relationships suggest, in most analysis, a relationship between 
<taxonomicName id="B8EE4889B927499CAD3C69B3AA702816" baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1825" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Odontocheila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Odontocheila nodicornis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nodicornis">
<emphasis id="E9014EC58218C6FFC7FA770FBC4F8242" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Odontocheila nodicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="93244797715B077AD61D1EF1890D20F3" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Phyllodroma" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Phyllodroma luteomaculata" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteomaculata">
<emphasis id="52AA5319328C412CE4F9A28B37CC0A41" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Phyllodroma luteomaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and in many of them, also between 
<taxonomicName id="76FBF8FCA9CAA31833214066B4B1A161" baseAuthorityName="Brulle" baseAuthorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pentacomia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pentacomia speculifera" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speculifera">
<emphasis id="6F7EC6A5F04F6EFAE4F7787AD63CA435" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Pentacomia speculifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="510A03C6801ABC60869C2C68BC6B1AC5" genus="Mesachantina" lsidName="Mesachantina chalceola" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" rank="species" species="chalceola">
<emphasis id="C5EB30EA7BE92542505A06C438820AB0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Mesachantina chalceola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As already pointed out by 
<bibRefCitation id="3030649599A2437CFF8B46F65FEE86B4" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4127.2.3" author="Moravec, J" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="276 - 300" refId="B29" refString="Moravec, J, 2016. Taxonomic and nomenclatorial revision within the Neotropical genera of the subtribe Odontocheilina W. Horn in a new sense - 16. Pentacomia (Mesochila) procera (Chaudoir), P. (M.) conformis (Dejean), and P. (M.) proceroides sp. nov. (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). Zootaxa 4127 (2): 276 - 300, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4127.2.3" title="Taxonomic and nomenclatorial revision within the Neotropical genera of the subtribe Odontocheilina W. Horn in a new sense - 16. Pentacomia (Mesochila) procera (Chaudoir), P. (M.) conformis (Dejean), and P. (M.) proceroides sp. nov. (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4127.2.3" volume="4127" year="2016">Moravec (2016</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="63EF42611F0B4862420313F2C4382783" author="Moravec, J" journalOrPublisher="Acta Musei Moraviae, Scientiae Biologicae (Brno)" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" pagination="127 - 206" refId="B30" refString="Moravec, J, 2018a. Taxonomic and nomenclatorial revision within the Neotropical genera of the subtribe Odontocheilina W. Horn in a new sense - 20. Beckerium W. Horn stat. restit., Mesochila Rivalier stat. nov. and Poecilochila Rivalier stat. nov. Acta Musei Moraviae, Scientiae Biologicae (Brno) 103 (2): 127 - 206" title="Taxonomic and nomenclatorial revision within the Neotropical genera of the subtribe Odontocheilina W. Horn in a new sense - 20. Beckerium W. Horn stat. restit., Mesochila Rivalier stat. nov. and Poecilochila Rivalier stat. nov." volume="103" year="2018 a">2018a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="457C651670D80A73BDFC8646BB17F66D" author="Moravec, J" journalOrPublisher="Biosfericka rezervace Dolni Morava: Lednice na Morave, Czech Republic" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" refId="B31" refString="Moravec, J, 2018b. Taxonomic revision of the Neotropical tiger beetle genera of the subtribe Odontocheilina - Volume 1. Odontocheila Laporte de Castelnau, Cenothyla Rivalier and Phyllodroma Lacordaire (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). Biosfericka rezervace Dolni Morava: Lednice na Morave, Czech Republic" title="Taxonomic revision of the Neotropical tiger beetle genera of the subtribe Odontocheilina - Volume 1. Odontocheila Laporte de Castelnau, Cenothyla Rivalier and Phyllodroma Lacordaire (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae)." year="2018 b">b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="0E0E6722C82B98E233477B7406F20DD0" author="Moravec, J." journalOrPublisher="Biosfericka rezervace Dolni Morava: Lednice na Morave, Czech Republic" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" refId="B32" refString="Moravec, J., 2020. . Taxonomic revision of the Neotropical tiger beetle genera of the subtribe Odontocheilina - Volume 2. A complete revision of other twelve genera of the subtribe (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). Biosfericka rezervace Dolni Morava: Lednice na Morave, Czech Republic" title=". Taxonomic revision of the Neotropical tiger beetle genera of the subtribe Odontocheilina - Volume 2. A complete revision of other twelve genera of the subtribe (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae)." year="2020">2020</bibRefCitation>
), the 
<taxonomicName id="184BEC0ECFF905131B81092FE53338DF" authorityName="Bates.The" authorityYear="1872" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pentacomia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pentacomia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CF17F4AFE3C3B93B3F4A74931B2A8B50" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Pentacomia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
former subgenera are probably not phylogenetically related, due to several morphological differences. The most conspicuous one is the uniformly shaped protarsi in both sexes in all 
<taxonomicName id="E1AF2AD289E574B22A11F468301ECA47" authorityName="Bates.The" authorityYear="1872" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pentacomia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pentacomia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="12BA8064D28B782D32D10EA583945DAD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Pentacomia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (unique character in the subtribe and within majority of 
<taxonomicName id="E7E76793464309B4E35EFBA21EB7BE05" class="Insecta" family="Cicindelidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cicindelidae</taxonomicName>
). The same goes for 
<taxonomicName id="C8C00D5EEA966A612DBF79D6EC94232A" authorityName="Laporte de Castelnau" authorityYear="1834" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Odontocheila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Odontocheila" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0203FE5B7D39BA36B6674CD8C2E341AE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Odontocheila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="46D88C9889D264BEFA3FAF3479A2C290" authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1843" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Phyllodroma" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Phyllodroma" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A39D3C26812B3CFC0EB020F71013B509" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="117">Phyllodroma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, that share an aedeagus flagellum, but with very different morphology and most probably homoplastic (Moravec, 2018b). Only a broader analysis, including representative taxa from all 
<taxonomicName id="89B069820A39978259057793C349C110" authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1843" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Phyllodroma" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Odontocheilina">Odontocheilina</taxonomicName>
genera may give better understanding of the group relationships.
</paragraph>
